 Bhisho - The Eastern Cape Government on Wednesday said that it is considering appealing the High Court judgement that ordered the dissolution of the Makana municipal Council. "The Judgement made by the Grahamstown division of the High Court of South Africa about dissolution of the Makana Municipal council has far reaching implications and the Eastern Cape provincial government is considering appealing the Judgement," Mvusiwekhaya Sicwetsha, Spokesperson for Eastern Cape Premier, Oscar Mabuyane. "Therefore the application/effect of the Judgement of the Grahams Town division of the High Court of South Africa will be suspended until such time as a final decision is taken in this regard." Details of the Eastern Cape Government's Appeal of this Judgement of the Grahamstown division of the High Court of South Africa will be communicated by the provincial government when the application for the leave to appeal is filed with the court. "The provincial government remains committed to ensure that Makana Municipality functions effectively and with efficiency in providing municipal services to the people of Makanda as per their constitution." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 